  "comments": "<p>Coins dated 1666 and 1667 have shield of <u>type 1</u>: with pointed bottom and large cut upper angles (as the one in pictures)<br>Coins dated 1668 and 1669 have shield of <u>type 2</u>: always with pointed bottom, but also with pointed upper angles that are no more cut. The shield shape may be more elongated and rectangular-like.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>This coin type was countermarked by the Bishopric of Salzburg in 1681.</p>",
